  'You are performing a government locational analysis at 412 Reedy Fork Road, Greenville, SC 29607. The subject is 3BR/2BA · 1,760 SF · 2004-built SFR · Reedy Fork Corridor. VA purchase appraisal. Veteran borrower. Lender: Navy Federal Credit Union. Pre-appraisal review by the lender''s VA compliance officer has identified three potential MPR concerns at this address: (1) the lot falls within the 65 dB DNL noise contour for GSP''s instrument approach path; (2) a SCDHEC-registered dry cleaning solvent site (PCE) is documented approximately 0.25 miles north; and (3) a partial Zone AE designation on the rear lot is indicated on the current FEMA FIRM panel. The appraiser must address all three conditions and all additional locational factors. Section 5 — Locational Influence — requires you to identify which locational factors are present at the subject, classify each as Positive, Negative, Neutral, or Market-Dependent based on the location profile evidence, and write a brief market-supported rationale for each classification. Government appraisals require dual-lens analysis: each factor must be evaluated for both market value impact and program-specific compliance implications (VA MPRs, HUD Handbook 4000.1, condemnation before-condition, etc.). Distractor factors that are not present must be left unchecked, and each rationale must cite specific evidence from the location profile and address any compliance implications relevant to this assignment type.'
