  'intermediate',
  '318 Waterside Court, Chesnee — Lake Blalock with HOA 30-Day STR Cap',
  'You are performing a specialty locational analysis at 318 Waterside Court, Chesnee, SC 29323. The subject is 3BR/2BA · 1,940 SF · 2015-built SFR · Waterside at Lake Blalock. Specialty appraisal — Lake Blalock community property with deeded HOA water access. The specialty characteristics are: (1) deeded community lake access in a second-home and vacation market; and (2) an HOA covenant that restricts short-term rental stays to a maximum of 30 days per year. The client intends personal vacation use with periodic STR income. The appraiser must address how the HOA STR restriction interacts with the locational factors and the client''s intended use. Section 5 — Locational Influence — requires you to identify which locational factors are present at the subject, classify each as Positive, Negative, Neutral, or Market-Dependent based on the location profile evidence and the specialty framework, and write a brief market-supported rationale for each classification. Specialty assignments require the appraiser to identify the relevant specialty characteristics first (waterfront tier, ADU, STR, mountain market, etc.) and then analyze every locational factor through the lens of those characteristics simultaneously. Distractor factors that are not present must be left unchecked, and each rationale must cite specific evidence and connect the factor to the relevant specialty framework.'
